Spec: SpecDD Task Skill

Purpose:
  Guide agents in finding, adding, interpreting, organizing, or updating `Tasks` entries in SpecDD `.sdd` files.

Owns:
  ./specdd-task/SKILL.md.ejs
  ./specdd-task/agents/openai.yaml

Must:
  Read the applicable spec chain for the requested scope, including inherited constraints.
  Focus task handling on task-bearing specs that apply to the requested scope.
  Update task status only after implementation and relevant checks are complete.
  Treat parent tasks as planning context unless directly targeted.
  Update task status only in the currently targeted spec unless instructed otherwise.
  Add tasks only when they are local, actionable, and consistent with inherited constraints.
  Keep task text concise and implementation-oriented.
  Use `[!]` for blocked work and `[?]` for unresolved design decisions.
  Use `[-]` only when the task is intentionally skipped and the reason is clear.
  Report task ids or exact task text, status changes, verification, and blocked or uncertain tasks.

Must not:
  Use task lines to override `Must`, `Must not`, `Forbids`, or write authority.
  Complete unrelated tasks opportunistically.
  Mark `[x]` before implementation and relevant checks are complete.
  Add or update tasks outside active authority.

Depends on:
  ../fragments/bootstrap-resolution.md.ejs
  ../fragments/spec-chain-resolution.md.ejs
